Absolutely fantastic! I served it with rice that had been lightly browned in oil prior to cooking.

Rating: 3
Really delicious fish! I used arctic char instead of trout and substituted all nonfat greek yogurt instead of the mayonnaise to make it healthier. Because my husband hates cilantro, we used flat Italian parsley instead and mistakenly bought roasted sunflower seeds instead of pumpkin seeds. We found the fish to be great, but the slaw was a little too dry and crunchy/fibrous. I'll definitely make the fish again, but I might skip the slaw.

Rating: 4
This was so easy and fast! The flavors are huge! This is a new favorite. I made the recipe as written 2 nights ago and then made just the slaw again last night, substituting shredded carrot for the jicama.

